ient it\'s highly unlikely that pesticides would be present. The Supplier\'s Certificate of Analysis tests for pesticide residue using AOAC 2007.01; the results don\'t detect residue and meets the USDA NOP requirements. However, in addition to this, we test for pesticide residue every fifth delivery of this ingredient (for each supplier company.)\\n\\nChlorella grows in fresh water but can also be grown organically in an artificial/indoor environment, such as a glass aquarium using fluorescent light. The supplier C of A doesn\'t specify how the chlorella is grown in China, but since fresh water can carry various contaminants (sometimes even more than sea water) this is another reason we independently test for pesticide residue (and heavy metals--see \\\"Heavy metals\\\" section of this page.) \", \"test_name\": \"Pesticides\", \"tests\": [{\"count\": 0, \"date_issued\": \"2024-05-16T22:56:03.499Z\", \"date_revised\": \"2024-05-16T22:56:03.499Z\", \"description\": null, \"file_pointer\": null, \"file_preview_pointer\": null, \"greater_than\": false, \"id_code\": null, \"less_than\": true, \"magnification\": null, \"method\": null, \"methods\": [\"AOAC 2007.01\"], \"odor\": null, \"required_spec\": false, \"sources\": [], \"statement\": \"The supplier C of A states that residue is \\\"not detected\\\" when the ingredient is tested with AOAC 2007.01 methodology.\", \"summary\": null, \"taste_dissolved\": null, \"taste_dry\": null, \"test_name\": \"Pesticide Residues\", \"type\": \"component_specifications/pesticides\", \"unit_of_measure\": \"\", \"url_preview\": null, \"visual\": null}]}, \"residual_solvents\": {\"date_issued\": \"2024-05-02T21:31:26.506Z\", \"date_revised\": \"2024-05-20T14:46:41.165Z\", \"file_pointer\": \"\", \"id_code\": \"\", \"locations\": {\"in_house\": false, \"primary\": \"supplier\", \"supplier\": true, \"third_party_lab\": true}, \"required_spec\": false, \"revision_number\": 6, \"statement\": \"Because of Chlorella\'s particular characteris